data.title: Kris Jenner files for divorce from Bruce Jenner
data.meta_description: Kris Jenner files for divorce from husband of 23 years Bruce Jenner
data.text:
Kris Jenner has filed for divorce from her husband of 23 years, Bruce Jenner.The documents, which were filed on Monday, cite irreconcilable differences, reports Us Weekly.Kris and Bruce will have joint custody of their youngest daughter, 17-year-old Kylie, who was the only child listed on the documents, filed at the LA Superior Courthouse. Kendall, 18, was not listed.

Kris has filed for divorce from her husband of 23 years, Bruce

According to TMZ, neither Bruce nor Kris will receive spousal support. The couple's divorce comes almost a year after they announced their separation. In October last year, the pair told E! News in a joint statement: "We are living separately and we are much happier this way. "But we will always have much love and respect for each other Even though we are separated, we will always remain best friends and, as always, our family will remain our number one priority."

The couple separated in October 2013
